<item>
            <title>[JDK-8299576] Reimplement java.io.Bits using VarHandle access</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8299576</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently, `java.io.Bits` is using explicit logic to read/write various primitive types to/from byte arrays. Switching to the use of VarHandle access would provide better performance and less code.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Also, using a standard API for these conversions means future VarHandle improvements will benefit Bits too.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Improvements in Bits will propagate to ObjectInputStream, ObjectOutputStream and RandomAccessFile.</description>
